  "prompt": "Why is John Wick called Baba Yaga?",
  "response": "John Wick is called \"Baba Yaga\" because of his legendary status as a hitman in the criminal underworld. In the first John Wick film, the character Viggo Tarasov refers to Wick as \"Baba Yaga,\" which is often translated to \"The Boogeyman.\" However, Viggo further clarifies that John Wick is not necessarily the Boogeyman, but rather the person you send to kill the Boogeyman. This nickname underscores Wick's reputation for being an unstoppable, almost mythical force within the assassin community, feared for his lethal skills and relentless efficiency.",
